      "title": "Expanding Your Reach: Group Discounts and Conditions",
      "content": "Group discounts are a fantastic tool to increase volume, fill seats, and build community buzz. However, they must be managed carefully to avoid cannibalizing your standard ticket sales. The key is to set clear **conditions and limitations**. A simple \"10% off for groups of 5+\" can be effective, but a more strategic approach is better.\n\nDefine the rules clearly: What is the minimum group size (e.g., 6+)? Is there a maximum number of discounted tickets? Is the discount only available for a specific tier? **Crucially, set a deadline** for group purchases, often aligning with the end of your early-bird period. This prevents last-minute group bookings from undermining your full-price sales window. Promote this as a \"Friends & Family\" or \"Team Building\" offer. In your CRM or sales system, have a clear process for designating a group leader, tracking the count, and applying the discount code. This structure turns group sales from an administrative headache into a scalable revenue stream."
